In Congress, I will continue championing policies that advance cutting-edge research, expand treatment options for our heroes, and ensure veterans receive the care they deserve.

LNG is one of the most promising energy solutions for the maritime industry. The Biden Administration’s attempt to classify domestic LNG bunkering as an export created unnecessary red tape that hurt American businesses and slowed innovation. My bill, the Cutting LNG Bunkering Red Tape Act, with @RepPfluger ensures that this growing industry has the clarity and certainty it needs to thrive—supporting jobs, strengthening our energy independence, and keeping our ports competitive.

I just introduced the Cutting LNG Bunkering Red Tape Act! This bill ensures that ship-to-ship transfers of domestic liquified natural gas (LNG) aren’t wrongly classified as exports–locking in @POTUS’s executive order that cuts red tape, supports American energy production, and increases job growth in Florida and across the country.

See my statement below on the passage of the One Big Beautiful Bill Act:

“This legislation gives Florida families real relief—protecting their paychecks, lowering their tax burden, and expanding opportunity. It makes the Trump tax cuts permanent, ends unfair taxes on tips and overtime, and preserves essential benefits like the child tax credit. It also strengthens critical programs like Medicaid and Social Security to ensure they work better and last longer. In addition, it empowers law enforcement to enforce our immigration laws and restore order at the southern border.

At its core, the One Big Beautiful Bill stands with the hardworking people who make our country strong—American families, small businesses, and the workers who are the foundation of Florida’s economy and our nation’s future.”
